reviews.title: 1.0 out of 5 stars Features without a sensible UI
reviews.author: Tobin E. Farrand
reviews.content: I worked as an Apple engineer for 10 years. I appreciate the attempt to jam an incredible amount of technology into a tiny space. Unfortunately the UI paradigm utterly fails. The UI has to be completely rethought. Even after repeated Google searches for how to do this or that, the watch resists all attempts at simplification. It is the MS DOS of the 21st century. Returned.

reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fantastic Starter Smart Watch
reviews.author: Hans
reviews.content: Many of the negative reviews here seem to come from customers who didn't do their research or have trouble using electronics in general. This watch is an amazing gift for anyone tech-savvy or looking to get into smartwatches. While the SE does have thicker bezels compared to the main Apple Watch Series, it's fully compatible with watchOS 11 and offers great battery life. For those concerned about compatibility, you can easily check on Apple’s website or read the product description. I recently bought this for a family member, and they absolutely love it!

reviews.title: 1.0 out of 5 stars I really wanted to like this Apple Watch
reviews.author: H9K097
reviews.content: My doctor recommended I buy a smartwatch to monitor heart rate. I chose the Apple Watch SE 2nd Generation, it had what I needed and was affordable. I purchased a better watch band (Apple), and a protective bezel (OtterBox).Within days of it arriving, the watch had issues with pairing. Having to pair several times was annoying, then many of my apps wouldn’t load, though they were rated as Apple Watch compatible (Apple App Store). Today the watch wouldn’t allow Apple Pay, and I found many complaints about this at various tech sites.I’m done with this product, not worth the money and certainly not worth the irritation.I’ve owned Apple products since 1977, many of them built well and long lasting. This Apple Watch SE 2nd Generation is not, in my opinion, one of their better products. 1 star, cannot recommend.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States October 13, 2024
reviews.product_attributes: Color: Midnight Aluminum Case with Midnight Sport BandSize: 40mm CaseStyle: S/M - fits 130-180mm wristsConfiguration: Without AppleCare+

reviews.title: 2.0 out of 5 stars Really let down
reviews.author: JJ
reviews.content: Got for the exercise capabilities and because Fitbit was so bad. This device might be worse. If I take less than 20 steps no data will be recorded. This is an issue in my field where I chunk in ten to twenty steps several times within a minute.The workout app always self pauses. I turned self pausing off and but I’m always hearing”work out paused”. Not very intuitive to use let alone start or end a work ok if it hasn’t needed it for you.Next to impossible to use their scribble board to type especially passwords.I have not had a good start to this experience. Most everything is hard to use or glitchy. Will update if I find this more user error.Watch does tell time well. If it can handle the time change then it will have raised the bar from my Fitbit that could really only tell time until time change.
